column1: So I got a hold of my sister.

And yes, she was angry, but she also said she'd
do her best to help.

That's a relief. Then we'll leave Zenkichi to
Niijima for now.

What should we do from here? We can't just sit
here and wait...

Akane-chan's been taken! It says if we want
her back, we have to go to Inari Taisha!
Huh!? The hell's that supposed to mean!?

Taken... You mean kidnapped!? Why? She's got
nothing to do with us!
I don't know... I'm just going off of the message she sent us.

Y'guys think, maybe Akane's just messin'
around?

Akane-chan doesn't know our other identities.
And even if she did, she wouldn't trick us.
True... Who would do such an awful thing?

Judging from the corner we're in, it's likely
Konoe or Owada.
So they're using Akane-chan just to lure us out!?
Given the timing, what else could it be?
What do we do? We can't even go to the cops...
What else is there to do!? We go after her!
Calm down a moment. This has to be a trap.

Yeah, they'd probably catch us within minutes
of stepping out the door.

But we can't just leave her. If they even lay a
finger on Akane-chan, I'll...!

Anyway, with Zenkichi-san behind bars, we're
the only ones who can save her.

If we put our own safety above that of an
innocent life, then we have no right to call
ourselves phantom thieves!

I'm well aware what this is, and I'm fine going
out there alone. You guys stay here and hold
the fort.
It's too risky to go alone.

You losin' it? We'd never let a friend risk
their neck without at least givin' backup.

Plus, Akane-chan's our fan. She knows more
than anyone we never abandon people in need.
Otherwise, we couldn't live up to our name.

Even if it is a trap, let's turn the tables against
them!

Darn right, Haru! Let's show them how big a 
mistake they've made!

All right. I'll take point and guide you past
trouble. Sophia, you navigate.

Okay, got it. I'll find the quickest and safest
route there.
